<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A130924379BFC69C680FC10" pageId="3" pageNumber="425" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A130924379BFC69C680FC10" blockId="3.[151,1437,921,1093]" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A130924379BFC69C74AFC7B" bold="true" box="[151,274,921,947]" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="FDBB4D060A1309243516FC6BC496FC7C" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[538,718,922,948]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlogothamnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutaedeagus">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A1309243516FC6BC496FC7C" box="[538,718,922,948]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">P. acutaedeagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from the latter by the forewings without spots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
